Ask HN: Things that have made you a better programmer
text:
"Things" is by intention ambiguous as it can vary from person to person. For someone it may be an enlightening course on Programming Languages; for someone else it can be a lengthy project they built from scratch. Or it maybe anything that doesn't come to my mind at the moment but have helped you up your game as a programmer.

After all, programming is another form of design.

Ask HN: Why is AirDrop so slow?
text:
I'm logged in to Apple on my iPhone and my macbook. Wifi + Bluetooth both on. I try to Airdrop a copy of a website I have on my phone to my desktop.... and it just says "Waiting" and I've typed this entire post while still waiting.

In the past it's done this and sent it after a while but I don't understand why it's not instant? What's the tech stack of Airdrop and what am I missing?
